casebody.data:
Thomas F. STROTHER, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. EXXON CORPORATION, Exxon Pipeline Co. and/or Exxon Pipeline, Inc., Defendants-Appellees. No. 77-2695

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. April 26, 1978. Aaron Frank McGee, Eunice, La., for plaintiff-appellant. E. Burt Harris, I. David Warner, III, New Orleans, La., for defendants-appellees.

Before THORNBERRY, GODBOLD and RUBIN, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5 Cir.; see Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Co. of New York et a1., 5 Cir 1970 431 F.2d 409, Part I.

 PER CURIAM:

The appeal is DISMISSED without prejudice to a future appeal following the district court’s review of the magistrate’s report and entry of final judgment by the district court. Kendall v. Davis, 569 F.2d 1330 (CA5, 1978).
